      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GISSELLE (7) is back from a break of six-and-a-half months and looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a recent trial. Was racing consistently last time in, heading to the paddock off a string of placings. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line and if she gets the gaps could make a winning return. JACQUELYN JOY (2) put the writing on the wall when runner-up from wider two back then was successful from the back row last week, getting home by 2.4 metres at this circuit and distance. Up in grade but should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. BETWEEN DECKS (9) draws on the back row but was solid in a stronger race last start and scored at this circuit and distance prior. TRIED AND TRUSTED (6) didn't do a bad job when fourth at Menangle last time out and recorded back-to-back seconds prior. Has been freshened but was kept ticking over with two trials.",
